UBX-MGA-DBD messages are only intended to be sent back to the same receiverthat generated them.Navigation database entry. The data fields are firmware specific. Transmission of this typeof message will be acknowledged by MGA-ACK messages, if acknowledgment has beenenabled (see the description of flow control for details).The maximum payload size for firmware 2.01 onwards is 164 bytes (which makes themaximum message size 172 bytes).
